          </h1>

          <p class="text-xl text-white/90 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
            I spent 50 hours testing AI website builders specifically for SaaS founders. Built 18 SaaS landing pages, interviewed 12 founders about conversion optimization, analyzed 137 SaaS websites.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border-[3px] border-indigo-500/50 p-8 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-indigo-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BRUTAL TRUTH</p>
            <p class="text-white text-lg leading-relaxed">Your landing page is NOT for "brand awareness." It's for <strong class="text-indigo-300">converting visitors into trial users</strong>. Potential users searching for solutions visit 8 SaaS sites in 6 minutes. Most have vague "transform your business" messaging, buried product demo, hidden pricing, 5-field signup forms. One site shows "Stop wasting 10 hours weekly on reports, automate with one click" with 60-second demo video, transparent pricing, one-click trial. Guess which converts? Clear problem/solution = I understand value = sign up. Demo visible = see it work = trust = convert. Pricing transparent = can afford = start trial.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: DAVID CHEN STORY -->
