          <p>Three months ago, David Chen reached out. SaaS founder: "ReportGenie" - automates weekly client reports for agencies. Good product, terrible landing page.</p>

          <p>His site: generic template, hero said "Transform your reporting workflow" (meaningless), 3 blurry screenshots, pricing hidden behind "Contact Sales" form. Signup required: name, company, email, phone, role, team size. 7 fields.</p>

          <p>Conversion rate: 0.8%. He's frustrated. "I'm spending $8K/month on ads. Getting 5,000 visitors. Only 40 sign up for trials. Something's wrong."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Hero: "Transform your reporting workflow with AI-powered automation." Vague. Three small screenshots of dashboard. Benefits: "Save time, increase accuracy, scale faster." Generic. Pricing: "Contact Sales for pricing" - hidden. Signup: 7 fields including phone number. Conversion: 0.8%. Most visitors bounced without scrolling past hero.</p>
        </div>

